# AGENTS.md

This file configures AI Agents working in this repository with the skills and context
needed for `terraform-provider-azurerm` development.

## Skills

The following skills are loaded from
[terraform-provider-developer-skills](https://github.com/jackofallops/terraform-provider-developer-skills).
Each skill provides the agent with step-by-step instructions, code patterns, and guardrails
for a specific class of work.

| Skill | When to use |
|---|---|
| `deprecate-property` | Deprecating or renaming a resource property for v5.0 |
| `deprecate-resource` | Deprecating an entire resource or data source for v5.0 |
| `modify-native-resource` | Adding a property to a native `*pluginsdk.Resource` |
| `modify-typed-resource` | Adding a property to a Typed SDK (`sdk.Resource`) resource |
| `migrate-to-typed-resource` | Converting a native resource to the Typed SDK wrapper |
| `resource-framework-migration` | Migrating a resource from `terraform-plugin-sdk` to `terraform-plugin-framework` via `internal/sdk` |
| `state-upgrade-required` | Implementing a state migration for schema or value changes |
| `preflight-validation` | Adding Azure Preflight Validation to a resource's `CustomizeDiff` |
| `provider-test-patterns` | Writing `basic`, `complete`, and `requiresImport` acceptance tests |
| `run-acceptance-tests` | Running and diagnosing `TestAcc` tests, including VCR replay |
| `provider-docs` | Creating or updating documentation in `website/docs/` |
| `terraform-dag` | Debugging parallel test failures and DAG-related race conditions |

## Conventions

- **Breaking changes** are gated behind `features.FivePointOh()`. The default (non-gated) code path must always be the v5.0 behaviour.
- **Typed resources** implement `sdk.Resource` with a `*Model` struct and `tfschema` tags. Use this pattern for all new resources and when migrating existing ones.
- **Documentation** changes must be included in the same PR as the schema or code changes they describe.
- **Acceptance tests** use `acceptance.BuildTestData` for deterministic names. Do not call `uuid.New()` or `time.Now()` in test configs.
- **Acceptance tests** require Azure credentials (`ARM_*` env vars). If these are not available to you, ask the user to run the test and return the output. Use `TC_TEST_VIA_VCR=replay` where a cassette exists to avoid real API calls.

## Repository layout (key paths)

```
internal/
  services/<service>/          # Resource and data source implementations
  sdk/                         # Typed SDK wrapper (sdk.Resource, sdk.ResourceMetaData, etc.)
  features/                    # Feature flags (features.FivePointOh(), etc.)
  preflight/                   # Preflight validation helpers
website/
  docs/
    r/                         # Resource documentation
    d/                         # Data source documentation
    actions/                   # Action documentation
    functions/                 # Provider function documentation
    ephemeral-resources/       # Ephemeral resource documentation
    list-resources/            # List resource documentation
    5.0-upgrade-guide.html.markdown  # Breaking changes upgrade guide
```

